    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3172_1.jpg"/>

                <!--<note type="libraryMark" rend="pencil">1910</note>-->

                <note rend="red-pencil" hand="other" style="transform:rotateZ(-90deg)">
                    <persName ref="#ps:FlorenceHenniker">Hon. Mrs Henniker</persName>
                </note>

                <opener>
                    <address rend="letterhead">
                        <addrLine>13, Stratford Place, W.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine rend="transform:rotateZ(-40deg)">TELEPHONE 3924 GERRARD</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    <dateline>
                        <date when="1910-05-30">May 30.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My dear friend:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>One line to say I am so glad you will be able to come to luncheon on <hi
                        rend="underline">Thursday</hi> next at 1.45. I am so <pb n="2"
                        facs="uoedh_hl_h.3172_2.jpg"/> sorry <persName ref="#ps:EmmaHardy">Mrs
                        Hardy</persName> has been so knocked up. My love to her.</p>

                <p><placeName ref="#pl:MelburyHouse">Melbury</placeName> looked too lovely for
                    words!</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute><choice><abbr>Yr</abbr>
                            <expan>Your</expan></choice>
                        <choice><abbr>aff.</abbr>
                            <expan>affectionate</expan></choice> friend</salute>
                    <signed>FH</signed>
                </closer>

            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
